The article discusses the joint vision for the alliance between the United States of America and the Republic of Korea. The two countries are building an alliance to ensure a peaceful, secure, and prosperous future for the Korean Peninsula, the Asia-Pacific region, and the world. The alliance is based on shared values, mutual respect, and a commitment to free democracy and a market economy. The United States-Republic of Korea Mutual Defense Treaty remains the cornerstone of the security relationship, guaranteeing peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula and in Northeast Asia. The alliance is adapting to changes in the 21st-century security environment and will maintain a robust defense posture. The Republic of Korea will take the lead role in the defense of Korea, supported by the U.S. military force presence. The article also mentions the importance of strengthening economic, trade, and investment relations, as well as cooperation in areas such as clean energy research and the peaceful uses of nuclear energy. The alliance aims to build a better future for all people on the Korean Peninsula, promote respect for human rights, and work jointly with regional institutions to foster prosperity and peace in the Asia-Pacific region. The two countries will also cooperate on global challenges such as terrorism, proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, climate change, poverty, and epidemic diseases. Proven bilateral mechanisms will be used to realize the shared vision for the alliance.